Riki.

What?

Good teamwork?
Yeah.

That sounds...

We have only been practicing whatever by ourselves so far.

Soy sauce!
Mayonnaise.

Worchestershire.

Is that how it works?

The most important thing for teamwork is for your feelings to be known to the other.
Worchestershire sauce on your eggs?
Seriously?
It is good.
You put mayonnaise on yours, Haru-chan?
Your hearts as one, all as one!
Do not you usually eat eggs with mayonnaise in salad?
To share passion!
For all members to be of one heart!

I do not put anything on them.
No way!
No way from me too!
Yes, this is youth!
That is horrible.
This is what I wanted!
You should put something on them.
Why?
I like the original taste of foods!
We are starting practice now!
All right!
Food time, food time!
The Little Busters are in perfect condition as usual.

Are you taking it?
I have already filled out the form.
I am thinking of taking it too.
I took it last year, so...
No thanks.
Not worth my time.
What?
Come on!
You were in the top ten nationwide last year!
Top ten for English?!
You are amazing!
I am jealous!
Kurugaya-san, you are a genius,
and your boobs are like, boom!
Compared to you, I am...
Yui-chan's invincible.
No one can beat her.
I told you, do not call me Yui-chan.
What about you, Kengo?
I have got a prefectural kendo tournament coming up.
I do not have time.
Rin-chan, what is wrong?
I think she is embarrassed that we saw her debating whether or not to take it.
A-Are you taking it, Kud?
Should I?
I do not think I will do well...
Oh, I know!
Why do not we each help Kuu-chan with our best subjects?
I see.
We coach her in our best subjects.
You are good at English, right, Komari-san?
Math and physics are Miss Nishizono's strengths.
I can do that.
If you need my help, I will do anything in my power.
You are good at a lot of stuff, are not you, Riki-kun?
There is not anything I am bad at,
but there is not anything I am good at either.
Um...
I hope it is not too much trouble...
It is okay!
You teach yourself when you teach others.
Feel free to ask me if you need any help.
Okay, then!
Thank you!
Thank you too, Riki!
Suddenly, it is just Riki.
Komari-chan...
Yes, Rin-chan?
Can you teach me too?
Yup!
You too!
Let us all get rid of our weak subjects!
Now for Operation Help Kuu-chan with Her Tests!
We will start with English!
This is exciting!
Before you start using your head,
you need to eat something sweet.
The raisin cheesecake is really good today!
Th-That is what you start with?
And you eat the plain muffins with some apricot jam.
That really hit the spot!
Wafu!
Burp.
It is about time we started now.
Start what?
Oh, right!
English!
Let us start with syntax.
I wish that it was the peaceful world tomorrow.
Try translating it!
Okay!
I wished that it war peacefull world tomollow.
I washed the world tomorrow in that it was doing peace!
It was doing peace?
What is it?
You are washing the world tomorrow?
Wafu!
D-Did I get it wrong?
It was not wash, it was wish.
It might be better if we started with vocabulary.
Let us make a vocab word list with Rin-chan!
I am sorry.
Math and physics!
Thank you very much!
You are always among the top-ranked students, Nishizono-san.
You are good at every subject.
Is there a trick to it?
Not really.
You just need to listen to the teacher in class.
And always remember to review.
But if you did not do that...
What should we do?
Yoohoo!
The star always arrives late!
Hey, Kud-o!
You are in bear hands now that I am here!
Bear hands?!
You are going to get eaten.
When you are short on time, you got to guess and cram!
If you are a woman, you got to guess and cram!
Should not it be act cute?
So what do you guess we cram?
Tell us, Mio-chin!
She is not guessing it?!
Do not look at me like that!
Well, guess there is nothing I cram do!
Get it?!
It was so good that you are completely speechless!
Say something, please.
Open your books to page 67.
A-Amazing!
She just ignored the whole thing!
I died.
Wafu?
Oh?
So Nishizono's teaching you math and physics, Kud-o?
Nishizono-san was really good at teaching!
We learned a lot too.
Then I will give you this, Kud-o!
I highlighted everything that is important.
Every word in here is highlighted...
Wafu!
I see, Inohara-san!
You are telling me everything in here is important!
Oh wow, this is great, Kud-o!
Red braised seaweed?
We are going to be working all night, so I put a lot of work into our snacks.
Freeze-dried tofu and rolled omelettes?
You are from out of the country, but you are good at making Japanese food.
My grandpa loves Japan very much.
He taught me all about Japan.
There she is!
She is that funny little quarter-Japanese.
Wow!
She is eating with chopsticks!
And it is seaweed too!
Hey, say something!
I hear you are really cute when reading aloud!
Look here...
I am going to get some soy sauce.
Hey, she is taking the proficiency test, right?
How is it looking?
We are taking bets on how bad she is going to do!
The odds are 8 to 2 for her failing right now.
It is just too much fun watching her.
It will be boring if she gets a good score!
She is cuter when she is her foolish self!
Kud...
Listen, you!
Move.
You are blocking the aisle.
Good grief.
Disgusting pigs.
They did not mean anything bad.
Anyone would talk about something exotic or foolish that they found.
That is just how it is.
Do not trouble yourself over it, Noumi.
I am fine.
I was just a little disappointed.
Just a little.
About this much.
You are all helping me so much!
I am actually fired up!
Fired up like a rocket!
We are pulling an all-nighter tonight!
The climate in the tundra is...
Oh, right.
Was not your grandpa Russian?
Yes.
Grandpa was born here.
The shores of the Baltic?
My parents were always busy, so it was my grandpa who raised me.
Grandpa worked with an old friend of his from Glavcosmos.
Glavcosmos?
The space agency of the Former Soviet Union.
Right.
So I went all around the world for his work.
France, England, Italy, Germany, Sweden!
That is pretty much most of Europe.
Yes.
India, Sri Lanka, America, Canada...
But I think only Brazil in South America.
You have been everywhere!
I only spent six months to a couple years in any one place though.
Where did you stay the longest?
Tevua, I think.
Tevua?
Where is that?
A small island nation right below the equator.
It is not on most maps.
The Republic of Tevua.
As part of the Former Soviet Union,
there is a lot of tension between the natives and the immigrants that moved there post-19th century.
The sky and the seas around there are beautiful.
My whole family has dual citizenships.
I was born on Tevua, so I have dual citizenship in Tevua and Japan.
Dual citizenship?
So you are a citizen of both nations?
Sounds like the circumstances surrounding you are quite complicated.
Kudryavka?
What luck.
Here is the book I borrowed from you.
Kanata-san!
It looks like a really difficult book.
It is Dewitt and Everett.
What?
Deviling Tablet?
I think you heard that wrong...
Dewitt and Everett are famous researchers in quantum mechanics for proposing the many-worlds theory.
Many-worlds theory?
You and Futaki-san can read books that advanced?
It is really interesting!
I stay up all night whenever I start reading!
But you might want to stop writing notes in the margins.
Chapter 2
Quantum States
and Everett's
Many-Worlds
Interpretation
What is that?
It is Russian.
New Sputnik Project?
I was reminded of it, so I wrote it down.
Come now.
This is ammonium perchlorate and hydrazine.
Hazardous corrosive substances used in rocket fuels.
Why would you think of something so dangerous?
I remembered taking the hazardous materials handling exam.
Hazardous materials handling exam?
Is not that an international exam?
It is what I do in my spare time.
I read through prep books for international exams.
I guess gaining more knowledge is a hobby of mine.
It is like learning new recipes.
Is it weird?
Well, I guess people have different hobbies.
Yeah, I had so much fun talking to Kanata-san last night
about the many-worlds interpretation and the role of geometry in the movements of the planets!
Wafu!
It was a lot of fun, but...
It is not very useful on a test.
I am really bad at filling in those bubbles.
You mean on the answer sheets?
When I think about the time limit, I get nervous,
and then I make mistakes.
Even though it is nothing compared to the many-worlds interpretation.
You are so weird.
Completely unbalanced.
Yoohoo!
Sorry I am late!
Onee-chan said she would help me study, so...
I have been waiting for you.
You are always late.
Hey, hey, do not get mad.
Oh, and Kudryavka,
make sure you do not fill in your answers in the wrong rows in the coming test.
Filling in answers in the wrong rows?
Kanata-san gave me some sample tests the other day.
And every time...
It seems getting easily distracted is a problem for you, Kudryavka-kun.
I hope you do well.
Kud's never gone to school before.
So simple things like time limits and answer sheets are completely foreign to her.
On the other hand, it is shocking how much she knows about things she is interested in.

I think that gap is what makes you who you are.
You think so?
You do not like that?
I cannot stay like this forever.
With anything that I do, it always feels like I am not quite there...

Calculate your own score.
